<p>
<a name="resulting-state">@EM{{@Vte{{}}@HI{{iru}}}}</a> is used to describe a state which is the result of the action expressed
by the verb. If the verb describes an action that can be repeated or continued,
@EM{{@Vte{{}}@HI{{iru}}}} expresses the continuation of that action. Otherwise if the
verb expresses a momentary action, @EM{{@Vte{{}}@HI{{iru}}}} expresses the idea
that the action happened and the resulting state continues. Verbs used in this construction
are intransitive ones.

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{window}}ga@KJ{{proportion}}re@EM{{teimasu}}.}}
